Bin-Packing & Wastage LogicStandard JSON data often forgets that you can't buy "half a bar." Your system must account for:Bar Lengths: GPS 45M 01, GPS 45GH 02, and I-sections come in 2500MM lengths.Wastage: The system must sort required cut lengths (descending) and fit them into bars to minimize waste.Horizontal Profile Exception: The SD36-HZ12B and SD36-RH13B are 1800MM.2. Missing Sub-Components: Miscellaneous HardwareThe following items were in your reference but often get left out of high-level BOMs:Assembly Brackets: Every Stile Door requires 4 nos of Stile Door Assembly Brackets at ₹165 each.Saddle Plates: These come in Black (₹672) or Silver (₹655) and are crucial for specific floor configurations.Gasket Calculation: Partitions require a perimeter-based gasket calculation ($2 \times [width + height]$) at ₹25 per running metre.3. Missing Strategic Flags: The "Safety" DataTo keep the AI from making promises you can't keep, these flags must be in the JSON:Chrome Floor Spring Lock: Always quote "EXCLUDING LOCK" until a specific model (OPL-1E vs OPL-1) is confirmed by you.Door Closer Silver: The price is not updated, so the system must block this option to prevent under-quoting.Annealed Glass: Prices are not updated; the system should only allow Toughened Glass quotes for now .

